1114.6, 1084.5, 1137.7]}, {"text": "of committed amounts as well as customer-specific one-time events. In addition, the acquisition of Prolexic", "bbox": [150.1, 1139.6, 1051.1, 1162.7]}, {"text": "during the first quarter of 2014 contributed to increased revenue.  These contributions to higher revenue were", "bbox": [150.1, 1164.6, 1066.6, 1187.7]}, {"text": "partially offset by lost committed recurring revenue and price declines.", "bbox": [150.1, 1189.6, 741.3, 1212.7]}, {"text": "The increase in our revenue from 2012 to 2013 was also driven by increased demand for our services,", "bbox": [187.6, 1239.6, 1041.3, 1262.7]}, {"text": "partially offset by the divestiture of ADS in the first quarter of 2013.", "bbox": [150.1, 1264.6, 720.0, 1287.7]}, {"text": "For the year ended December 31, 2014, resellers accounted for 25% of revenue as compared to 21% and", "bbox": [187.6, 1314.7, 1063.8, 1337.7]}, {"text": "22% of revenue, respectively, for the years ended December 31, 2013 and 2012. For the years ended December", "bbox": [150.1, 1339.7, 1082.8, 1362.7]}, {"text": "31, 2014, 2013 and 2012, no single customer accounted for 10% or more of revenue.", "bbox": [150.1, 1364.7, 857.4, 1387.7]}, {"text": "Effective in the first quarter of 2014, we elected to revise our method for determining the split of revenue", "bbox": [187.6, 1414.7, 1070.7, 1437.8]}, {"text": "derived from our operations located outside the U.S. Previously, revenue was split based on our invoicing", "bbox": [150.1, 1439.7, 1036.1, 1462.8]}]}